The "Cool Walk" and "Cool Skip" is one one of the 6 ESSENTIAL dribbles needed for effective guard play. "Ball turning," not carrying, is one of the 14 #Ball #Control Principles needed to develop into a #monster handler! The Cool Walk/Skip is THE most important dribble concept that can be taught.

The "Cool Walk/Skip" allows for you to:

1. Control Pace and defender (won't be sped up) without body contact unless #neccessary
2. Handle Pressure/Protect the Ball
3. Transition seamlessly into protection breakdowns or faceup atttacks
4. Patiently wait for plays
*5. Conserve energy
6. Flow 
7. Offset defensive quickness and size in most instances
